text:
Sixth Ave., east side, north from and including West 48th to and including West 51st Streets, showing Rockefeller Center (Radio City). In the right foreground is seen the Center Theatre (was temporarily called Roxy Theatre) at the S.E. corner of West 49th Street. North of it is the smaller unit (16-stories) of the R.C.A. Building from West 49th to West 50th Streets; the 70-story R.C.A. structure appearing slightly eastward and facing on Rockefeller Plaza. In silhouette is visible the 31-story R.K.O. Building, from West 50th to West 51st Streets.
1933.

Wurtz Brothers.
